HEADWORD: Oxymoron
<hw>Ox`y*mo"ron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/<?/<?/, fr. <?/<?/<?/ pointedly foolish; <grk>'oxy`s</grk> sharp +
<grk>mwro`s</grk> foolish.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure in
which an epithet of a contrary signification is added to a word; e. g.,
<xex>cruel kindness</xex>; <xex>laborious idleness</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

